Nevertheless, experts believe that if Beijing plays its cards well, China can benefit from the effects of the trade war in the long term by reducing the interdependence of the two economies.
"The fact that a quick political decision in either Washington or Beijing could create the conditions for economic turmoil in both countries is actually much more dangerous than many observers have previously recognized," says Abigail Grace, a research associate focused on Asia at the Center for New American Security think tank.
Syria is 'ready' for the return of refugees, the Foreign Minister said.
Syria says it is ready for the voluntary return of refugees and asks for help to rebuild the country devastated by the over seven-year war.
In a speech to the United Nations General Assembly, Foreign Minister Walid al-Moualem stated that the circumstances in the country are improving.
"Today, the situation on the ground is more stable and safer thanks to progress made in the fight against terrorism," he said.
The government is rebuilding the areas destroyed by terrorists in order to bring about normality.
All conditions were now in place for the voluntary return of refugees to the country, which they had to leave due to terrorism and unilateral economic measures aimed at their everyday lives and livelihoods.
The UN estimates that over 5.5 million Syrians have left the country since the war began in 2011.
Another six million people still living in the country need humanitarian aid.
Al-Moualem said the Syrian government welcomed assistance in rebuilding the devastated country.
However, he stressed that it would not accept conditional aid from countries that had supported the insurrection.
Europe succeeded in winning the Ryder Cup in Paris
Team Europa won the 2018 Ryder Cup and defeated Team USA with a final score of 16.5 to 10.5 in the Le Golf National near Paris.
The US has now lost six consecutive times on European soil and has not won a Ryder Cup in Europe since 1993.
Europe won the crown back after the team of Danish captain Thomas Bjorn reached the 14.5 points it needed to defeat the United States.
American star Phil Mickelson, who had problems over much of the tournament, sunk his tee off at the 16th track (Par 3) in the water and lost to Francesco Molinari.
Italian golfer Molinari was able to shine in all his rounds and became one of 4 players who scored a 5-0-0 since the tournament began in its current format in 1979.
American Jordan Spieth was beaten 5–4 by the player with the lowest ranking in Team Europe, Thorbjorn Olesen from Denmark.
The player with the world's best ranking, Dustin Johnson, lost 2 to 1 against the Englishman Ian Poulter, who possibly played his last Ryder Cup.
Spaniard Sergio Garcia, veteran from eight Ryder Cups, became the best European Ryder Cup player of all time with 25.5 career points.
“Normally I don’t cry, but today I couldn’t hold back.
It was a difficult year.
I am so grateful that Thomas chose me and believed in me.
I'm so infinitely happy to win the cup back.
It's about the team and I'm glad to have made a contribution," said the emotional Garcia after the European victory.
He passes the torch on to his compatriot John Rahm, who won 2–1 in the individual encounters against American golf legend Tiger Woods on Sunday.
I'm so incredibly proud to have beaten Tiger Woods, whom I've been watching on TV since my childhood," said 23-year-old Rahm.
Woods lost all his four games in France and now has a Ryder Cup balance of 13-21-3.
A curious statistic for one of the greatest players of all time who has won 14 important titles and is only surpassed by Jack Nicklaus.
The USA team had trouble finding the fairways all weekend, with the exception of Patrick Reed, Justin Thomas and Tony Finau, who have done high-profile performances throughout the tournament.
American captain Jim Furyk said after a disappointing performance of his team: “I’m proud of the boys, they’ve fought.
There was a time this morning when we had put pressure on Europe.
We didn't do anything about it.
Hat off for Thomas.
He's a great captain.
All of his 12 players performed well.
We will regroup, I will talk to the PGA America and our Ryder Cup Committee and we will look forward.
I love these 12 guys and I'm proud to be their captain.
You have to pull the hat.
We were defeated."
Red Tide Update: Concentrations in Pinellas, Manatee and Sarasota decrease
The latest Florida Fish and Wildlife Commission report shows that there is a general decline in red tide concentrations in parts of the Tampa Bay area.
According to the FWC, in the areas of the districts of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte and Collier, more gapy flowering conditions are recorded, indicating declining concentrations.
A red algal bloom extends over approximately 130 miles of coastline from north Pinellas to south of the Lee district.
Spots can be found about 10 miles off the coast of Hillsborough District, however, compared to previous week in fewer places.
A red tide was also observed in the Pasco district.
In the last week, mean concentrations were reported in or off the coast of the Pinellas district, low to high concentrations off the coast of the Manatee district, background to high concentrations in or off the coast of the Charlotte district, background to high concentrations in or off the coast of the Lee district, and low concentrations in the Collier district.
Respiratory complaints continue to be reported from the Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier districts.
No new respiratory problems were reported in northwest Florida during the last week.
